ZH: 他总是很善于恭维别人。
EN: He is always good at complimenting others.

ZH: 她经常用恭维的话语来鼓励他人。
EN: She often uses flattering words to encourage others.

ZH: 你不需要为了讨好别人而恭维他们。
EN: You don't need to flatter others just to please them.

ZH: 我不喜欢听别人的恭维，我更喜欢实质性的帮助。
EN: I don't like hearing flattery, I prefer substantial help.

ZH: 尽管他们恭维他的才华，他仍然保持谦虚。
EN: Despite their compliments on his talent, he remains humble.

ZH: 他恭维了她的外貌，让她感到很高兴。
EN: He complimented her appearance, making her feel happy.

ZH: 当人们对我恭维时，我总是感到有些不自在。
EN: I always feel a bit uncomfortable when people flatter me.

ZH: 她恭维了他的厨艺，因为她真的很喜欢他做的饭菜。
EN: She complimented his cooking skills because she genuinely liked the food he made.

ZH: 我不是在恭维你，但你的新发型真的很好看。
EN: I'm not just flattering you, but your new hairstyle really looks good.

ZH: 她对孩子们的表演感到非常喜爱，于是给他们恭维了一番。
EN: She loved the children's performance so much that she complimented them.

ZH: 恭维太过分的话会让人感到不真实。
EN: Excessive flattery can make people feel insincere.

ZH: 他总是用漂亮的措辞进行恭维。
EN: He always uses beautiful language to compliment others.

ZH: 接受别人恭维的同时，我们也要学会感谢。
EN: While accepting compliments from others, we should also learn to express gratitude.

ZH: 别人对我恭维，我会以同样的方式回应。
EN: If someone compliments me, I will respond in the same way.

ZH: 他天生就喜欢向人恭维，这是他的特点。
EN: He has a natural inclination to flatter others; it's his characteristic.

ZH: 她总是用独特的方式来表达恭维之意。
EN: She always expresses her compliments in a unique way.

ZH: 他的恭维让她的自信心得到了提升。
EN: His compliments boosted her self-confidence.

ZH: 别人的恭维可以激励我们做得更好。
EN: Compliments from others can motivate us to do better.

ZH: 她的恭维不仅是为了讨好别人，更是出于真心。
EN: Her compliments are not just to please others, but also sincere.

ZH: 恭维是一种社交技巧，但要注意真实性。
EN: Flattery is a social skill, but one should be mindful of its authenticity.

ZH: 在适当的场合，恭维可以增进人际关系。
EN: Compliments, when given in appropriate situations, can strengthen interpersonal relationships.
